description.narrative: Girls and boys and their mothers living in humanitarian conditions have access to life saving nutrition interventions from pregnancy to adolescence., which contributes to Early Childhood Development, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Improved and equitable use of high-impact maternal, newborn, child health and nutrition specific and sensitive interventions.
